# KEEP THIS FILE RULE-FREE.
#
# On Cloudflare Pages, _redirects rules are followed even when a static asset
# matches the request ("Redirects are always followed, regardless of whether
# or not an asset matches"). A SPA catch-all like "/*  /  200" therefore
# rewrites EVERY request — hashed JS/CSS bundles, fonts, sw.js — to the HTML
# shell, which took the whole site down in July 2026.
#
# SPA fallback comes from the platform instead: because this project ships no
# top-level 404.html, Pages serves the root shell for any path with no
# matching asset, so deep links and hard refreshes work with zero rules here.
# (Adding a top-level 404.html silently disables that fallback — don't.)
